    {
      "type": "cultural_note",
      "title": "Serbian Family Values & Slava",
      "content": "Family is the cornerstone of Serbian society. Extended families remain closely connected, and it is common for multiple generations to live together or very near each other. Sunday family lunches are a widespread tradition. The most distinctive Serbian family tradition is 'Slava' (Слава), the celebration of a family's patron saint day. Each Serbian family inherits its Slava from the father's side, and it is passed down through generations. The celebration involves a special ritual bread called 'slavski kolač,' wheat (žito/koljivo), wine, and a candle. The priest blesses the bread, and guests come throughout the day to celebrate. UNESCO recognized Slava as an Intangible Cultural Heritage of Humanity in 2014. When invited to someone's Slava, it is customary to bring a gift — wine, flowers, or sweets are all appropriate choices."
    }
